<br>
This gripe came to me at 1:00 am, after I worked an entire day, so, I was rather tired and irritable. An excuse? No... but it is the reason for my lack of caring. Plus the fact that I was hunting giants with a small group and didn’t have time to deal with it with the care that I normally could have, not without suffering a XP lost of 3 to 3 1/2 blue, either to Vivienne or her hunting companion.<br>
<br>
Before this complaint came to me, I just received a /tell from a player that I have known for some time who was in the Nek/Neriak area. He informed me that he was listening to the obnoxious /shouts from the complaining individual all night - and that he basically got what he deserved (“being a dink” was the phrase used, amongst others). Why would he do this? We aren’t close friends, just happened to have been in Sel’quar together. Who shall I believe? A person that I have known a long time, somebody I know with integrity not to take sides (and who Aailan essentially called a liar)... or a random voice, somebody that I do not know. I was being fed two sides of the same story, and each side was in opposition.<br>
<br>
But, what was the greatest cause of my irritation with the whole mess was the fact that just that night, I was trained twice by a bard pulling numerous giants and cyclops’. The first time I have to run to the zone (thank god for J-boots) and the second time I saw her run right past, with a giant or two in two, but I had time to get Vivienne out of the way. Their reason for the train? Vivienne was sitting in the spot they have been pulling down for the past 3 hours, even though she was there for at least 1/2 an hour with no bard running by. My point is, I was pissed, and I dealt with it... with the bard and her group in question... I did NOT go to her guild leader (as a leader playing Vivienne the way I do, I have enough things to deal with in regards to my own character, and I wouldn’t want to bother another leader with something I can handle with the offending party myself). Neither did I threaten GMs or black-balling on a public forum, which is what has been done, and is being done here.<br>
<br>
Do I condone training? Not really, I would NOT do it to somebody myself. But, like I said, if I was attacking Felwithe, and a young highelf brought the guards down on me (which I effectively see as summoning the guards /shrug) I would have dealt with the guards by either killing them or running to zone. Either way, I wouldn’t have faulted the young one for their actions (especially if I was overheard uttering obnoxious /shouts) as I faulted the bard in Rathe Mountains. I might even compliment them on going beyond their means to drive Vivienne out of their city.<br>
<br>
If Aailan or his companion died as a result of Mythria’s train, I would have ensured a 96% resurrection for him at the soonest possible time (as my cleric friend with her epic was awake at the time), and even dragged the corpse to the zone myself. But, they didn’t die, they made it to the zone, and instead of dealing with it with the offending player herself, he chose to involve others, insult every member of my guild on a public forum and run to the GMs for a rather minor transgression in the grand scheme of things. It could have been dealt with simply with the offending party, but no, Aailan went out of his way to try and get Mythria in trouble with me (and I know he said that, confirmed by two parties).<br>
<br>
In essence, I was tired and irritated already, and his “running to the teacher” only served to irritate me even more, so I do apologize for not dealing with this issue appropriately as befitting the leader of the Sisters of Myth, now that I have had time to relax and look upon the events with clearer eyes. It is just sad that he couldn’t wait before slamming me and my guild in such a manner before it could be dealt with civilly, at a better time for everybody. <p>What is the point of living if life is not spent dancing on the edge of the razor-blade?<BR>
