5) If my client did mean to do it, and was sane at the time, she was acting in self-defense.<br>
<br>
We're moving backwards here, from #5 to #2.  Usually, this progresses in the other direction. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>
-Monique Wittig, "The Straight Mind"<BR>
